<p rend="chapter">Naradakkha thomanā āsīsa</p>

<p rend="subhead">3. Gāthā</p>

<p rend="hangnum" n="1"><hi rend="paranum">1</hi><hi rend="dot">.</hi></p>

<p rend="gatha1"> Pālito <pb ed="M" n="0.0592" /> pāḷiyā cheko,</p>

<p rend="gatha2">Tvaṃsi gambhīra-ñāṇavā;</p>

<p rend="gatha3">Pāliyāva pālitassa,</p>

<p rend="gathalast">Dadāmidāni bho ahaṃ.</p>

<p rend="hangnum" n="2"><hi rend="paranum">2</hi><hi rend="dot">.</hi></p>

<p rend="gatha1"> Dakkhāvādesu <pb ed="M" n="0.0593" /> kusalo,</p>

<p rend="gatha2">Pālito sāsanandharī;</p>

<p rend="gatha3">Piṭakesu ajjhogāyha,</p>

<p rend="gathalast">Naradakkhaṃbhisaṅkharī.</p>

<p rend="hangnum" n="3"><hi rend="paranum">3</hi><hi rend="dot">.</hi></p>

<p rend="gatha1"> Suta-dharena <pb ed="M" n="0.0595" /> racitaṃ,</p>

<p rend="gatha2">Etaṃ sāra-gavesino;</p>

<p rend="gatha3">Atandikā su-dakkhantu,</p>

<p rend="gathalast">Aggagga-sāsane ratā.</p>

<p rend="title">Naradakkha thomanā āsīsa</p>

<p rend="subhead">2. Gāthā</p>

<p rend="hangnum" n="1"><hi rend="paranum">1</hi><hi rend="dot">.</hi></p>

<p rend="gatha1"> Ñuṃ <pb ed="M" n="0.0596" /> pālitodha jāto yo,</p>

<p rend="gatha2">Thero so abbhutova ñuṃ;</p>

<p rend="gatha3">Ñuṃ mahā-pālito santo,</p>

<p rend="gathalast">Nikāya-pālito ca ñuṃ.</p>

<p rend="hangnum" n="2"><hi rend="paranum">2</hi><hi rend="dot">.</hi></p>

<p rend="gatha1"> Ñuṃ <pb ed="M" n="0.0598" /> nara-dakkha-ganthaṃ yaṃ,</p>

<p rend="gatha2">Sovakā nara-dakkha-daṃ;</p>

<p rend="gatha3">Narā dakkhantu sammā ca,</p>

<p rend="gathalast">Dakkhattaṃ pāpuṇantu ñuṃ.</p>
